results.name: Decimal expansion of q between 0 and 1 maximizing Dedekind eta function eta(q) = q^(1/24) * Product_{n>=1} (1 - q^n).
formula: Root of the equation Sum_{k>=1} A000203(k) * r^k = 1/24. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Jun 28 2017
mathematica: q /. Last @ FindMaximum[ DedekindEta[ -I*Log[q]/(2*Pi)], {q, 1/25}, WorkingPrecision -> 200] // RealDigits[#][[1]][[1 ;; 100]]& // Prepend[#, 0]&
x /. FindRoot[24*Sum[DivisorSigma[1, k]*x^k, {k, 1, 1000}] == 1, {x, 1}, WorkingPrecision -> 101] (* _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Jun 28 2017 *)
